when you eat always the fork in the left side of the hand why i'm left handed and i eat with my fork in the left hand for things that don't require cutting if i am cutting i have the fork in my right hand and cut with my left hand for more knife control i do one other different thing with my fork when i have a knife in my left hand and that is i pick up my meat etc with the fork prongs facing downward european style this gives me more control of my less controlled hand also a note for place settings all items with four letters in the word go on the left left letters fork dish for bread dish while all items with five letters go on the right right letters knife spoon glass drink Table setting Chinese cuisine Chopsticks Kosher foods Spork Knife Fork Sandwich Breakfast Russian cuisine Jewish cuisine Korean cuisine Customs and etiquette of Japan Roman eating and drinking Japanese tea ceremony Cuisine of Thailand Spaghetti Cuisine of Denmark Spoon Barbecue Happy Tree Friends Cuisine of Singapore Meal Bread French fries Eucharist Bong Cuisine of the Philippines Kashrut Domesticated turkey Glass MRE Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban German cuisine Mango Soup Magic (illusion) Burger Resident Evil (video game) Shogi Bengali cuisine Tool Cajun cuisine Chess strategy and tactics Cha chaan teng Steak Timpani McDonald's D__ner kebab Cuisine of Laos Iron Chef Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Pizza Paella Passover Cuisine of Malaysia Potato Muslim ibn Aqeel Culture of Ancient Rome Battle of Cut Knife Unclean animals The Amber Spyglass Halaal Burns supper The Subtle Knife Japanese cuisine 613 mitzvot French cuisine Chicago-style pizza Aztec Tuning fork Fondue Lathe Initiation: Silent Night, Deadly Night 4 RuneScape quests Joke Historical roots of Catholic Eucharistic theology Soul food Card game Rugby union Sausage Pea soup Tofu British cuisine Ramen Dairy Pasta RuneScape skills Yu-Gi-Oh! anime and manga characters Cuisine of Brazil Mushroom hunting Glossary of n